product of two vectors can be defined as the product of the magnitudes of t=
he two vectors and the cosine of the angle between the two vectors. Thus, <=
span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-m=
ath-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math dis=
